'''Husam Ali Mohammad Abu Dahab''' ({{langx|ar|حُسَام عَلِيّ مُحَمَّد أَبُو ذَهَب}}, born 13 May 2000) is a [[Jordan]]ian [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who is a [[Defender (association football)|center-back]] for [[Kuwait Premier League]] club [[Al-Salmiya SC|Al-Salmiya]], on loan from [[Al-Faisaly SC|Al-Faisaly]], as well as the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
===Al-Faisaly===
On 16 December 2023, Abu Dahab renewed his contract with Al-Faisaly until the end of the 2027 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=الفيصلي يجدد عقد اللاعبين زكريا وأبو الذهب |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%B5%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AC%D8%AF%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%B2%D9%83%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%88%D8%A3%D8%A8%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B0%D9%87%D8%A8-1547916 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |language=Arabic |date=16 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=الفيصلي يجدد عقدي نجميه |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1293444 |website=Kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |language=Arabic |date=16 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=الفيصلي يجدد الثقة باللاعبين خالد زكريا وأبو الذهب |url=https://royanews.tv/news/316607 |website=royanews.tv |publisher=Roya News |language=Arabic |date=17 December 2023}}</ref>

On 26 May 2024, Abu Dahab contributed with a goal for Al-Faisaly, in a 6–2 victory over [[Shabab Al-Ordon SC|Shabab Al-Ordon]] during the [[2023–24 Jordanian Pro League]] season.<ref>{{cite web |title=لقب.. بـ " لون الذهب " |url=https://www.addustour.com/articles/1420629-%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A8-%D8%A8%D9%80-%C2%AB-%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B0%D9%87%D8%A8-%C2%BB |website=addustor.com |publisher=Ad-Dustor |language=Arabic |date=26 May 2024}}</ref> He was recognized as a standout defender for Al-Faisaly that season, which caught the eye of the new national team manager [[Jamal Sellami]] to call him up to the senior team.<ref>{{cite web |title=جمال سلامي ينصف لاعبا من المنتخب الأردني |url=https://www.analkhabar.com/%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%B5%D9%81-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF/ |website=analkhabar.com |publisher=Ana Al-Khabar |access-date=6 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=14 July 2024}}</ref>

On 24 July, [[Al-Faisaly SC|Al-Faisaly]] announced that they renewed Abu Dahab's contract until the end of the 2028 season, as well as for the intent on loaning him out to [[Kuwait Premier League]] club [[Al-Salmiya SC|Al-Salmiya]] for the [[2025–26 Kuwaiti Premier League|upcoming season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=وافقت الهيئة الإدارية المؤقتة للنادي الفيصلي على إعارة لاعب فريقنا حسام أبو الذهب لنادي السالمية الكويتي لمدة موسم واحد، متمنين له التوفيق والنجاح في محطته الاحترافية الجديدة . |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/DMfzW6BIioI/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA== |website=instagram.com |publisher=alfaisalyscjo |access-date=24 July 2025 |language=Arabic |date=24 July 2025}}</ref> However, on 20 September 2025, Abu Dahab returned to Amman due to Al-Salmiya not being able to register any player to their club.<ref>{{cite web |title=حسام أبو الذهب يعود بعد تعثر انتقاله للسالمية الكويتي |url=https://www.addustour.com/articles/1518263-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%A3%D8%A8%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B0%D9%87%D8%A8-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AB%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%AA%D9%8A |website=addustour.com |publisher=Ad-Dustor |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=20 September 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Abu Dahab's first international match with the Jordan national team was against [[North Korea national football team|North Korea]] in a friendly on 29 August 2024.<ref>{{cite web |title=تفاصيل مباراة الأردن و كوريا الشمالية |url=https://jfa.com.jo/arsh_match.php?id_mon=1&id1=1103 |website=jfa.jo |publisher=Jordan Football Association |access-date=6 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=29 August 2024}}</ref> His first competitive match was against [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]] for [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|World Cup qualifying]] on 5 September 2024 in [[Amman]], which Jordan drew 1–1.<ref>{{cite web |title=اتحاد الكرة يعلن غياب التعمري عن مباراة فلسطين |url=https://sawaleif.com/%D8%A7%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%BA%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7-915608/ |website=Sawaleif.com |publisher=Sawaleif |access-date=6 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=6 September 2024}}</ref>

